Aim:- Write a program to implement various String operations in Python

Algorithm:-

Step 1: Start
Step 2: Input a string from the user.
Step 3: Display the original string.
Step 4: Find and display the length of the string using len() function.
Step 5: Convert the string to uppercase using upper() and display it.
Step 6: Convert the string to lowercase using lower() and display it.
Step 7: Input a substring and find its position in the string using find().
Step 8: Input old and new substrings and replace them using replace() function.
Step 9: Split the string into words using split() function.
Step 10: Input two strings and concatenate them.
Step 11: Check whether the concatenated string is alphabetic using isalpha().
Step 12: Check whether the concatenated string is numeric using isdigit().
Step 13: Display all results.
Step 14: Stop.


Code:- #String Operations

s = input("Enter a string: ")

print("Original string:", s)
print("Length of string:", len(s))
print("Upper case:", s.upper())
print("Lower case:", s.lower())

sub = input("Enter a substring to find: ")
print("Position:", s.find(sub))

old = input("Enter the old string: ")
new = input("Enter the new string: ")
print("After replacement:", s.replace(old, new))

print("Split string:", s.split())

str1 = input("Enter first string: ")
str2 = input("Enter second string: ")

concat = str1 + str2

print("Concatenation:", concat)
print("Is Alphabetic?", concat.isalpha())
print("Is Numeric?", concat.isdigit())


